4.4 Analysis
Ablation Study. In this subsection, we further conduct ablation studies to verify the effectiveness of each component in UTP. As seen in Table 4, both the universal MLM and CMCR have a signiÔ¨Åcant impact on the UTP performance enhancement, demonstrating the efÔ¨Åciency of the approach that we have proposed. For instance, removing MLM and CMCR could make the model performances decrease to 88.51 and 88.90 in R@50, separately. Besides, we also can observe that L(rt, rw) loss plays the most important role in our proposed CMCR as it can directly align the modalities of pure text and table.
Hyper-parameter Analysis. Intuitively, œÑ in Eq.7 has the effect on our model‚Äôs performances. Therefore, we conduct additional experiments to validate the inÔ¨Çuence of temperature œÑ on WIKISQL dataset. We validate the model performances with œÑ ‚àà {0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 1}. As shown in Figure 2, we show that our UTP obtains the optimal

